title: 'Jills Add First Women's Hockey Recruit
text:
'Jills Add First Women's Hockey Recruit 
By Zach Schneider 'Jills Add First Women's Hockey Recruit   12:58 PM CDT 
Ashland, WI (NNCNOW.com) --- The Northland women's hockey team has added forward Kylie Fahmer as its first-ever recruit ahead of the 2016-17 season, the school announced on Wednesday afternoon. 
Fahmer is a native of Fort Worth, Tex. and has played the past four seasons with the Dallas Stars 19U Elite team, which has gone to the USA Hockey national tournament two of the past three years. 
"Kylie is a talented player but an even better person," head coach Kelly Rider said, "and she's just the type of student-athlete we are looking for to help build our program's culture and foundation." 
Northland will begin play in the 2016-17 season.
